\i0\fs36 The Risk Menu
\fs24 \
 \

\b Colors...
\b0 :  This command puts the standard Next color panel on screen.  The only places in this version where you can use color are the Game Setup Panel and the Preferences Panel (both discussed below).\

\b Services
\b0 :  This menu command brings up a the standard Next services menu.\

\b Hide
\b0 :  Hides the application.  All windows go away, but the game still runs.  Any game in progress is preserved.\

\b Quit
\b0 :  Quits the application.  Any game in progress is abandoned.\
 \

\fs36 The Info Menu
\fs24 \
 \

\b Info Panel...
\b0 :  Information about the application such as the version number is in the Info Panel.\

\b Help...
\b0 :  The Help command asks the Workspace manager to open a browser on the Help directory.  You can double click on any of the help files to have Edit open them.\

\b Preferences...
\b0 :  The Preferences panel allows you to set certain application wide preferences.  Risk will remember your preferences.\
